.TH TRUSTMUX-CTL 1 "2026-05-28" "trustmux" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
trustmux\-ctl \- manage the Trustmux daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B trustmux\-ctl
.I COMMAND
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B trustmux\-ctl
starts, stops, and inspects the Trustmux daemon.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B setup
One-time setup: verify Tailscale is installed and connected, then
configure \fBtailscale serve\fP for HTTPS on port 7432.
.TP
.B start
Start the daemon in HTTPS mode via \fBtailscale serve\fP (default).
.TP
.B start\-local
Start the daemon bound to 127.0.0.1 only, for access via SSH tunnel.
.TP
.B start\-direct
Start the daemon with a self-signed TLS certificate, binding on
all interfaces for LAN access without Tailscale.
.TP
.B stop
Send SIGTERM to the running daemon.
.TP
.B restart
Stop then start the daemon in HTTPS mode.
.TP
.B status
Show whether the daemon is running and the URL to connect to.
.TP
.B log
Tail the daemon log at
.IR ~/.config/trustmux/trustmux.log .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/trustmux/trustmux.log
Daemon log file.
.TP
.I /tmp/trustmux.pid
PID file written at startup.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR trustmux (1),
.BR trustmux\-pair (1),
.BR trustmux\-enable (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Dustin Kirkland <kirkland@ubuntu.com>
